GENERAL INFORMATION 1. Title of project: VBA Senior Leaders Symposium in March 2020 Training 2. Scope of Work: Under this contract, the Contractor shall provide meeting space and in-house audio-visual equipment in support of the VBA Senior Leaders Symposium in March 2020 Training in Washington, DC. 3. Background: Conference space will be needed March 16-18, 2020, and AV equipment will be needed March 16-18, 2020 to discuss FY2020 and FY2021 targets and goals with an emphasis on the Under Secretary for Benefits three priorities, 1) Provide Veterans with the benefits they have earned in a manner that honors their service, 2) Ensure strong fiscal stewardship of the money entrusted to us by taxpayers, and 3) Foster a culture of collaboration. The role of the Director is managing and overseeing the work of VBA operations; so, this training will be focused on developing an executive-level understanding of how to successfully manage VBA operations. We will provide the opportunity to discuss topics such as organizational change management, modernization initiatives, accountability, how to improve service, and new ideologies and techniques for customer service. This training will also provide communication and training opportunities for VBA Regional Office Directors, Central Office Deputy Directors, and Central Office Directors to increase their ability to improve the employee experience. The training is required and is a re-occurring/annual event. 4. Performance Period: The period of performance is from March 16 through the end of the training on March 18 (the dates when the conference/meeting space and AV equipment will be needed). 5. Type of Contract: Firm-Fixed Price (FFP) 6. Place of Performance: Washington, DC 7.
